  "text": "NF-kB induces a number of downstream genes, including the IkB family. Among the IkB molecules, IkBa is highly induced by NF-kB activation [CITATION_1] . Having shown that PKC regulated NFkB activity in M-CSF-stimulated MDMs, we next determined whether inhibition of PKC activity decreased expression of NFkB-regulated genes. We treated both MDMs and RAW 264. To further define the role of PKC in mediating human MDM survival in response to M-CSF, we examined the expression of the anti-apoptotic gene BCL-xL, which is also regulated by NF-kB. As shown in Figure 6C , Ro-31-8220 reduced M-CSF-stimulated BCL-xL expression compared to cells treated with M-CSF and the vehicle control DMSO (p,0.05).",
